Both outputs are written and `transcript.json` validates against `transcript_schema.json`.

**Headline finding:** A near-complete 3-way interaction. Univariate associations of `feature_001`, `feature_014`, and `feature_021` with `objective_response` collapse once their joint distribution is examined. Only the triple-positive cell (n=2,401) is elevated (63.3% response vs ~16% in the other 7 cells). Two further binary suppressors (`feature_026` and `feature_009`) abolish the boost when either is positive.

**Best-supported treatment-effect subgroup** (treating `feature_021` as the candidate treatment — three are symmetric):
- Inside `feature_001=1 ∧ feature_014=1 ∧ feature_026=0 ∧ feature_009=0` (n=4,531): treatment lifts response from 15.8% → 78.6% (+62.8 pp).
- Outside this subgroup (n=45,469): no detectable treatment effect (−0.3 pp, p≈0.46).

A single binary indicator of the full responder phenotype achieves pseudo-R² 0.066, twice the 35-feature main-effect model. No continuous covariate further modified the within-subgroup effect (all p > 0.05). 15 iterations recorded.
